  "text": "iii. The process of freezing and thawing may break down structural integrity and also reduce bio-activity of functional proteins (like enzymes, etc.). However, it has not been shown that the nutritional value of macronutrients is significantly affected. Vieira et al. reported a 2% loss for protein and fat, but not for lactose, after one cycle of freezing and subsequent thawing (measured with Mid-IR). However, Berkow et al. did not report a loss after 3 repeated cycles [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
